# Get longitude values
lon <- ncvar_get(ncin,"lon")
nlon <- dim(lon)

# Get latitude values
lat <- ncvar_get(ncin,"lat")
nlat <- dim(lat)

# get time
time <- ncvar_get(ncin,"time")
tunits <- ncatt_get(ncin,"time","units")

# get temperature
tmp_array <- ncvar_get(ncin,dname)
dlname <- ncatt_get(ncin,dname,"long_name")
dunits <- ncatt_get(ncin,dname,"units")
fillvalue <- ncatt_get(ncin,dname,"_FillValue")

# get global attributes
title <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"title")
institution <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"institution")
datasource <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"source")
references <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"references")
history <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"history")
Conventions <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"Conventions")

# convert time -- split the time units string into fields
tustr <- strsplit(tunits$value, " ")
tdstr <- strsplit(unlist(tustr)[3], "-")
tmonth <- as.integer(unlist(tdstr)[2])
tday <- as.integer(unlist(tdstr)[3])
tyear <- as.integer(unlist(tdstr)[1])
chron(time,origin=c(tmonth, tday, tyear))
##  [1] 01/16/01 02/15/01 03/16/01 04/16/01 05/16/01 06/16/01 07/16/01
##  [8] 08/16/01 09/16/01 10/16/01 11/16/01 12/16/01

# replace netCDF fill values with NA's
tmp_array[tmp_array==fillvalue$value] <- NA

# length(na.omit(as.vector(tmp_array[,,1])))

# get a single slice or layer (January)
m <- 1
tmp_slice <- tmp_array[,,m]

# quick map
image(lon,lat,tmp_slice, col=rev(brewer.pal(11,"RdBu")))

# levelplot of the slice
grid <- expand.grid(lon=lon, lat=lat)
cutpts <- c(-40,-30,-20,-10,0,10,20,30,40)
levelplot(tmp_slice ~ lon * lat, data=grid, at=cutpts, cuts=11, pretty=T, 
          col.regions=(rev(brewer.pal(11,"RdBu"))))
